# claude-litellm — API keys and endpoints
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in your values.

# ----- Azure OpenAI (optional — leave blank to configure models via the UI later) -----
# If you fill these in, the baseline `linux/configs/litellm-config.yaml` will
# route to two Azure deployments named EXACTLY:
#     gpt-5.4        (used for ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_SONNET_MODEL and _OPUS_MODEL)
#     gpt-5.4-mini   (used for ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_HAIKU_MODEL)
# Your Azure resource must expose deployments with these names, OR edit
# linux/configs/litellm-config.yaml to match your actual deployment names
# BEFORE running setup.sh.
#
# If you leave these blank, setup.sh still completes — but you will need to:
#   1. Open http://127.0.0.1:4000/ui (user: admin, pw: the master key in
#      ~/.profile as ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN) and add at least one working model.
#   2. Edit ~/.profile and set ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_{HAIKU,SONNET,OPUS}_MODEL to
#      the Public Model Name(s) you configured. The same name may be used for
#      all three if you only have one model.
#   3. `source ~/.profile` (or relaunch your shell) before running `claude`.
AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=
# Resource endpoint URL (no /openai suffix, no trailing slash):
#   https://<resource>.openai.azure.com         (classic Azure OpenAI Service)
#   https://<resource>.cognitiveservices.azure.com (Azure AI Foundry / AI Services)
AZURE_RESOURCE_ENDPOINT=

# ----- Optional: LiteLLM master key (used for Anthropic auth) -----
# Sent by Claude Code as `Authorization: Bearer <token>`. Must start with "sk-".
# If unset, setup.sh auto-generates one as `sk-<48 hex chars>` on first run and
# persists it to ~/.profile + ~/.config/litellm/env. Subsequent runs reuse it.
# Set this only if you want to manage the key yourself.
# ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=sk-

# ----- Optional: Vertex AI (Gemini) — uncomment to enable -----
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/vertex-sa.json
# GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=your-gcp-project-id

# ----- Optional: Generative Language API (non-Vertex Gemini) -----
# GEMINI_API_KEY=

# ----- Optional: real Anthropic Claude through the gateway -----
# Forwards to api.anthropic.com when you add a model_list entry in /ui.
# Any Public Model Name works (the baseline config doesn't reserve `claude-*`
# names); pick one that starts with `claude` or `anthropic` if you want it to
# show up automatically in Claude Code's /model picker.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ----- Optional: external Postgres (skip local apt install) -----
# If set, setup.sh skips installing/configuring local Postgres and just plumbs
# this URL into LiteLLM. Format: postgresql://user:pw@host:5432/dbname
# DATABASE_URL=

# ----- LiteLLM UI ------------------------------------------------
# Browse to http://127.0.0.1:3457/ui
# Username: admin
# Password: the LITELLM_MASTER_KEY value (also exported as ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN
#          in ~/.profile after setup.sh runs).
# To override, set UI_USERNAME / UI_PASSWORD in ~/.config/litellm/env manually.
#
# NOTE: Claude Code's gateway model discovery only surfaces ids beginning
# with "claude" or "anthropic" in the /model picker — non-prefixed names
# (including the baseline `azure/gpt-5.4` entries) are reachable via the API
# and via `/model <full-id>` but won't auto-appear. If you want a /ui-added
# model in the picker, give its Public Model Name a `claude-` or `anthropic-`
# prefix. See https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway ("Model selection").
#
# Any provider env var you export in your shell or ~/.profile (e.g.
# OPENAI_API_KEY, GROQ_API_KEY, DEEPSEEK_API_KEY, …) is auto-forwarded to
# the LiteLLM daemon — you don't have to also list it here.
